description: For sale: $474,900. Located in King Field, this lovely updated home is one you don't want to miss. In every aspect of this charming 2 story home, you'll find the perfect balance of its original Minneapolis charm - combined with all your modern conveniences. Top to bottom, this home has been carefully redesigned and professionally upgraded! The main level is filled with its original character and boasts an updated kitchen featuring new appliances plus soft close drawers and cabinets. The lower level was designed for entertainment and also contains a 4th, non-conforming bedroom. The breathtaking remodeled upper level is an absolute master oasis which includes a walk-in closet, oversized master suite and en-suite bathroom complete with a custom steam shower retreat! Home also features 2 ductless mini-splits on upper and lower levels, plus 3 window units for main level that will be included in sale. Back and side yards were designed for entertaining as well with the addition of a new deck and side patio!

description: Recently sold: $1,398,000. Located on one of the most desires streets in Minneapolis this 1923 classic home features elegant spaces, hardwood floors, crown molding, high ceilings and architectural details of the time as well as the best of a 2015 major addition to the main level and lower level. High-end finishes from TEA2 architectures and top quality builder can be seen in every detail of the new spaces. The main floor features original spaces including a gracious foyer opening to the classic spindled stair case, the generous living room with wood burning fireplace, an office with fireplace and a wall of built-in book cases and a large formal dining room. Addition on the main level includes the totally new gourmet kitchen with premium appliances (Wolf, Asko, Sub-Zero) a large center island, granite countertops, breakfast bar and opens to the beautiful Great Room surrounded by large windows with wonderful views and filled with natural light. Quarter sawn hardwood floors have in-floor heating as well as forced air heat and central air conditioning. Main level also has a half bath. Great room opens to a 2 level deck on the south side of the home. Upstairs are 3 bedrooms. The large master bedroom has 2 closets (one with a sink) and opens to the full master bath with separate tub and shower. The 2 other bedrooms share a Jack and Jill bath and both are a very nice size. The lower level is also new and features a huge family room with stone surround of the gas-burning fireplace, in-floor heat, walk-out doors to the huge 1/3 acre lot, all new guest bedroom and all new ¾ bath. There is also ample storage and a room that would be perfect as a wine cellar. Picturesque setting on one of this historic street located just steps to Lake Harriet and to the Rose Gardens. Nearby are great restaurants, grocery stores, coffee shops and a public library. Dream home and dream location in the heart of the Minneapolis Chain of Lakes.

description:
For rent: $1,700. Completely updated 2 Bedroom 1 bathroom

This building sits less then 2 Miles from both Lake Calhoun and Lake Harriet. Get ready to spend your days walking, kayaking, or biking around Lake of the Isles, and enjoying all the perks of living in this convenient South Mpls location.

Within a block radius, you will hit the new pizza place, Grand Cafe, a delicious french Bistro with a brunch that is to die for and a wine bar you cannot beat. If you are looking for something a bit more vibrant, just across 38th St is Victors 1959 Cafe, where you can try some authentic cuban food you won't find anywhere else in MN! The same block also offers adorable boutiques, coffee shops and a yoga studio, so everything you need is within walking distance of this unit.

This two bedroom unit is perfect for anyone looking to enjoy the original character uptown Minneapolis has to offer. Featuring original hardwood floors and fantastic wood trim throughout, you will have the best of both worlds since there have been some updates in the kitchen and bathroom. Landlord takes care of all snow removal and lawn care. There is also a brand new washer dryer in the basement for the building to share. There is parking in the back and 2 available garages for rent, there is also a ton of on street parking since the street itself stays relatively quiet. All pets are allowed with a one time non refundable fee of $350 for dogs and $250 for cats.

Owner Pays Trash, Recycling, Water, Sewer, Snow, and Lawn Maintenance

description:
For rent: $1,980. Large Kingfield Duplex available now for move in. 3 Bedroom, 1 Bath, lower unit of duplex. $1980/month. Close to Kingfield's great restaurants, Uptown area and Lake Harriet. Short walk to bus lines.

The unit is wired for USI fiber Internet. Laundry is included, shared in basement.

Wood flooring throughout unit. Well-kept as it was previously owner-occupied. Fireplace mantle has outlet for TV hook-up or sound system. Dishwasher installation pending. 

Spacious living room and large, separate dining room. Plenty of closet and storage space in hallways and each bedroom. Additional basement storage possible.

3 Bedrooms flexible for guest room, roommates, exercise room, or a great office/work-from-home spaces.
Bedroom 1: 12' x 11'
Bedroom 2: 11' x 12'
Bedroom 3: 12' x 10'.
(Kingsized bed is show in photo).

1 Garage space available for $75/month additional. Garage is separated from other stalls to allow additional private storage. Plenty of on-street parking available in this quiet neighborhood.

Dishwasher pending installation.

Nonsmoking building
Cats ok, small dogs considered.

Security deposit of one month's rent.
Call or text or email Wendy at number/email provided.
Flexible on move-in dates, can move in mid-month.

Utilities ALL included except cable and internet, electricity. Already included in rent is heat, gas, and water.
